</p><p>One may also wonder whether it is necessary to use the entire set of square integers to write each natural as the sum of four squares. <a href="/wiki/Eduard_Wirsing" title="Eduard Wirsing">Eduard Wirsing</a> proved that there exists a set of squares <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">S</span> with <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle |S|=O(n^{1/4}\log ^{1/4}n)}">
